<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-435] Project quotas for ldiskfs require patched server kernel</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-435</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The manual mentions that project quotas are available when using the ldiskfs backend, but it does not mention that the servers must be running a Linux kernel with Lustre patches.&#160; Attempting to run the patchless server Lustre packages will results in the MDT failing to mount if project quotas are enabled.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Lustre 2.10.6&lt;br/&gt;
CentOS 7.6</environment>
